SIMPLE: sixtieth
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sixtieth
<hw>Six"ti*eth</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[As.
<ets>sixtiogo⟦edh⟧a</ets>, <ets>sixtigo⟦edh⟧a</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Next in order after the fifty-ninth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Constituting or being one one of sixty equal parts
into which anything is divided.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sixtieth</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sixtieth
<hw>Six"ti*eth</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The quotient of a
unit divided by sixty; one of sixty equal parts forming a
whole.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The next in order after the fifty-ninth; the tenth
after the fiftieth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sixty</ent>⟦br⟧
